<figureCitation box="[804,890,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–39" captionStartId="52.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[272,1323,202,1714]" captionTargetId="figure-98@52.[264,1323,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 28–39. Details of Ocypus vindex (28–31), O. quiris (32–37) and O. sericeomicans (38, 39). 28, 35—apical portion of median lobe, ventral view, paramere removed; 29—underside of paramere; 30—underside of apical portion of paramere; 31, 37—tergite 10 of female genital segment; 32, 38—sternite 9 of male genital segment (setation not shown in Fig. 32); 33, 39—tergite 10 of male genital segment (setation not shown in Fig. 33); 34—aedoeagus, ventral view; 36—underside of apical portion of paramere." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
